4. Add coriander, turmeric, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, pepper, lentils, broth, bay leaves, and crushed tomatoes. Stir and bring to a boil.

**Ingredients:**
- Olive oil
- 2 celery sticks, finely chopped
- 1 onion, finely chopped
- 1 carrot, finely chopped
- 3 garlic cloves, crushed
- 140g cubetti di pancetta
- 500g pork mince
- 500g beef mince
- 200ml milk
- 2 cans of chopped tomatoes
- 2 bay leaves
- 1 rosemary sprig
- 2 thyme sprigs
- 2 tsp dried oregano
- 2 beef stock cubes
- 500ml red wine
- Pasta sheets
- Parmesan cheese, grated
- 1.5 litres milk (for b√©chamel)
- 1 onion, thickly sliced (for b√©chamel)
- 3 bay leaves (for b√©chamel)
- 3 cloves (for b√©chamel)
- 100g butter (for b√©chamel)
- 100g plain flour (for b√©chamel)
- Nutmeg, grated

**Instructions:**
1. **Prepare B√©chamel Sauce:**
   - Combine 1.5 litres milk, 1 thickly sliced onion, 3 bay leaves, and 3 cloves in a large saucepan. Bring to a gentle boil, then turn off the heat and set aside for 1 hour to infuse.
   - Strain the milk and melt 100g butter in the same pan. Mix in 100g flour and cook for 2 minutes.
   - Gradually add the strained milk, stirring constantly to avoid lumps. Simmer until thickened. Season with salt, pepper, and nutmeg.

2. **Prepare Meat Sauce:**
   - In another large saucepan, cook celery, onion, carrot, garlic, and pancetta in olive oil until soft.
   - Add pork and beef mince, 200ml milk, and tomatoes. Break up the mince and add bay leaves, rosemary, thyme, oregano, stock cubes, and 500ml red wine. Simmer covered for 1 hour, then uncovered for 30-60 minutes until tender.

3. **Assemble Lasagne:**
   - Preheat oven to 180¬∞C (160¬∞C fan/gas 4).
   - Spread a spoonful of meat sauce in a 3.5-litre baking dish. Layer with pasta sheets, b√©chamel sauce, meat sauce, and parmesan. Repeat layers and finish with pasta, b√©chamel, and parmesan.
   - Bake for 1 hour until bubbling and browned.

### Wine Pairing
For the lasagne, consider pairing it with a medium-bodied red wine such as **Chianti**, **Montepulciano**, or **Sangiovese**. These wines have the necessary acidity and body to complement the rich flavors of the lasagne. A recommended choice is the **Antinori Villan Antinori Chianti Classico Riserva**, which has a 4.6 out of 5-star rating and costs about $36 per bottle.'}]

   - In a large saucepan, cook celery, onion, carrot, garlic, and pancetta in oil until soft.
   - Add both types of mince and cook, breaking up lumps with a wooden spoon.
   - Add milk, tomatoes, bay leaves, rosemary, thyme, oregano, stock cubes, and wine. Simmer covered for 1 hour, then uncovered for another 30 minutes to 1 hour until the meat is tender.

3. **Assemble and Bake:**
   - Preheat the oven to 180¬∞C (160¬∞C fan/gas 4).
   - Spread a layer of meat sauce in a baking dish, cover with pasta sheets, then b√©chamel sauce, and sprinkle with parmesan. Repeat layers, finishing with pasta, b√©chamel, and parmesan.
   - Bake for 1 hour until bubbling and browned on top.

Enjoy your homemade lasagne!'}]
